          "source_document_id": "src-scotiabank-html-21e9ee585879b087",
          "source_snapshot_id": "snap-8ec6e9fc4c133615",
          "evidence_chunk_id": "chunk-c6ba480bc45d89bc",
          "evidence_text_excerpt": "How is interest applied to this account?\nF irst, you earn a Regular Interest rate (and if you have an Ultimate or Preferred Package, the applicable Package Interest Rate Boost), which is applied to your daily closing balance and is paid monthly.\nSecond, you can earn a Premium Interest rate when you open a Premium Period(s), each of which can have a length of 90, 180, 270 or 360 days. For each Premium Period, Premium Interest is calculated by applying the Premium Interest rate to each deposit, and any paid Regular Interest, each day until the end of the Premium Period. Premium Interest is only paid at the end of the Premium Period, and only if no debit transactions were made within the Premium Period.",
